  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "# Feature Issue\n\n[Figma Design](https://www.figma.com/file/h9wo4GipgZURbqqr1vShFN/Communities-for-Mobile?type=design&node-id=15331-288514&mode=design&t=11ZK4xcYm0njxRrt-0)\n\n### User Story\n\n- As an existing community member\n- I want new accounts to be automatically shared with the community\n- So that I donâ€™t need to take any future action\n\n![image](https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/5999878/8e8685ca-f8ba-4f59-aa30-bed22b33d818)\n\n### Description\n\nThis feature aims to automate the process of sharing new accounts with the existing community. Whenever a new account is created, it should be automatically visible or shared with all existing community members. This process should be seamless and require no additional actions from current members. The feature should be integrated in a way that respects privacy and security standards.\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n\n- Follow Figma\n- New accounts should be automatically shared with all existing community members upon creation.\n- The process should require no manual action from either new or existing members.\n- The feature should be tested for both public and private community settings.\n\n\nDepends on: https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/issues/17969\n\n### Blocked By\n\n### Tasks\nstatus-go: \n  - [ ] Update Join Community API/Implement New API for the Toggle\n  - [ ] Implement logic to automatically Share Future Addresses if the feature is enabled.\n\nstatus-mobile:\n  - [ ] Implement Share all Addresses Toggle in Addresses for permissions Screen (status-mobile)",
